    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>SUING H.M.O.'S</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Anne Ruderman</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Ruderman, Anne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Senate unanimously approves bill to grant patients' right to sue health maintenance organizations for medical malpractice in denying or delaying care (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Senate unanimously approved a bill last week that would grant patients the right to sue their health maintenance organizations for medical malpractice in denying or delaying care. The bill would also permit patients to bypass an independent appeals process before filing suit. The measure is a crucial part of a 24-point Health Care Reform package developed by the Senate Health Committee. It now goes to the Assembly.</p>
        <p>Anne Ruderman</p>
      </block>
